      <trans-unit xml:space="preserve" id="4d87a341be664ccc" weblate-flags="md-text, safe-html, strict-same">
        <source>A fusion hound’s head is completely haloed in a seething mass of radioactive energy, so unlike traditional canines, it has no bite attack. Instead, it pounces on prey with its clawed forelimbs, which causes a burst of radiation to flare from its body, burning whatever it touches.</source>
        <target></target>
